Vice President Mike Pence and Second Lady Karen Pence visited Montenegro and were welcomed by Prime Minister Dusko Markovic and his wife. Pence thanked the Prime Minister for Montenegro's efforts in promoting regional stability. He also spoke at the Adriatic Charter Summit, emphasizing the need for unity in the face of threats and provocations. Before leaving, Pence and his wife met with the staff from the US Embassy in Montenegro and expressed gratitude for their service.